      • printHCN

        public static void printHCN(int lowerBound,
                            int upperBound)
        Prints all numbers that have a higher amount of divisors than the numbers before. Only checks numbers between lowerBound and upperBound. This function will only print HCNs after reaching the first real HCN in its range. Keep in mind that the first few numbers could have a smaller amount of divisors than a number lower than lowerBound and are therefore not guaranteed to be HCNs.
        Parameters:
        lowerBound - the number from where to start looking for HCNs
        upperBound - the last number to check

      • printHCN

        public static void printHCN()
        Endless HCN print. Has to be manually interrupted.

      • getHCNs

        public static int[] getHCNs(int upperBound)
        Returns an int[] with all highly composite numbers from 1 to upperBound.
        Parameters:
        upperBound - the upper bound to check to.
        Returns:
        an int[] with size HCNAmount that contains all HCNs from 1 to upperBound.
